</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF919F65A335952D8DB25AE59A131F32" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type material">
<paragraph id="7B4A73D2275A45E105A7B412F62E98F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F2B1FA9AC1DCADFAC4859A701CB30D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Holotype (original designation): NZSI M.2426 (registered 8 January 1894). Paratypes: specimens listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E100459E4F2D3BECE1D4F333037B8953" author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 9, 1885: 5), not found in the ZSI collections, perhaps misplaced when the collections were moved from the Indian Museum to ZSI (8-10 spms); the shell figured by Hanley and Theobald (1874 in 1870-1876: pl. 114, fig. 5), location unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="05916F8B7ED1501D49AA1222549C5327" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="shell dimensions">
<paragraph id="3598C7A0391D09952ADC7819FB97B8BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shell dimensions.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B3E1EBC90719F21BDC9623D94D8C661" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Holotype: SH 56.6 mm, SW 49.7 mm, AH 40.6 mm, AW 33.8 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="09584E3206B5640829334242721EFA89" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="81D1C28F3F1A5FB1294CC1796A0FEFDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECF3642CFC5F1FEE5B9A853E6C263F44" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="F78421865FE81212F2B3EF778F654DA5" author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 9) listed seven specimens from 
<normalizedToken id="6E9921E776085255788B1B4DDA2A31FF" originalValue="“Pegu”">&quot;Pegu&quot;</normalizedToken>
collected by Theobald, and one from 
<normalizedToken id="DCA4B0C1405203CA08CC2DEBA22F3180" originalValue="“Tenasserim?”">&quot;Tenasserim?&quot;</normalizedToken>
and one from 
<normalizedToken id="DE5B22BEF9795B796545C31CBC783723" originalValue="“Mandalay?”">&quot;Mandalay?&quot;</normalizedToken>
each with &quot;No history&quot;. He also noted that the shell illustrated by Hanley and Theobald (1874 in 1870-1876: pl. 114, fig. 5) was referable to this taxon; it is therefore also to be considered a paratype. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="19E316BAE41558262540010CFC6AB694" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.23978" author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B22" refString="Nevill, G, 1885. Hand list of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Part II. Gastropoda. Prosobranchia-Neurobranchia (contd.). Indian Museum, Calcutta [=Kolkata], x + 306 pp. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.23978" title="Hand list of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Part II. Gastropoda. Prosobranchia-Neurobranchia (contd.). Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], x + 306 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.23978" year="1885">Nevill (1885</bibRefCitation>
: 5) listed the seven Pegu specimens from Theobald (with &quot;type var.&quot;) but three (not one) from &quot;Tenasserim (?)&quot; and one from &quot;Mandalay (?)&quot;, all four from the collection of Stoliczka. Thus it is not clear whether there were eight or ten paratypes, as either 
<normalizedToken id="4279E59522106ED906263D61E234794E" originalValue="“one”">&quot;one&quot;</normalizedToken>
or 
<normalizedToken id="878CF9ACF256963CFC5DBF6CC2642949" originalValue="“three”">&quot;three&quot;</normalizedToken>
from 
<normalizedToken id="E421EA86462C6926E42A68AA0D1D5C11" originalValue="“Tenasserim?”">&quot;Tenasserim?&quot;</normalizedToken>
could be in error. 
<bibRefCitation id="9EA3AC9F9AA9A0D303B39778C5CD69DF" author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 10) gave measurements for the holotype and the shell height, at least, matches that of the present specimen (NZSI M.2426); shell width was given as 48 mm, while the present measurement is 45.6 mm, probably within the margin of error. We therefore consider it to be the holotype. None of the paratypes could be found in NZSI and the location of the specimen illustrated by Hanley and Theobald is unknown. The old specimen label associated with the holotype (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1B411156CE4301E280A479F57BDA5FA1" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Collection labels. A. Pachylabra angelica Annandale, 1920; NZSI M. 11649 / 2. B. Ampullaria erronea Nevill, 1877; NZSI M. 2404. C. Ampullaria conica var. expansa Nevill, 1877; NZSI M. 2426." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.47792.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371739" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">12C</figureCitation>
) is almost unreadable. However, a newer label (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D2061B4C4423366A5FD90DCC0B28FB81" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Collection labels. A. Pachylabra angelica Annandale, 1920; NZSI M. 11649 / 2. B. Ampullaria erronea Nevill, 1877; NZSI M. 2404. C. Ampullaria conica var. expansa Nevill, 1877; NZSI M. 2426." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.47792.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371739" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">12C</figureCitation>
) indicates Dr F. Stoliczka as the collector, although both this label and the register indicate 
<normalizedToken id="FDDA3D3DBF6272459932ED9EB40E3E51" originalValue="“Pegu”">&quot;Pegu&quot;</normalizedToken>
as the locality, with the collector indicated in the register as unknown, i.e. with a question mark (
<normalizedToken id="AB6CCFBD10E1E243C69FAAD50E12B028" originalValue="“?”">&quot;?&quot;</normalizedToken>
). Nevertheless, given that 
<bibRefCitation id="A022FF0401C4EB03703D14D53F86D521" author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 9, 
<bibRefCitation id="8F933F29A809F3A0ED788C361749A0F0" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.23978" author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B22" refString="Nevill, G, 1885. Hand list of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Part II. Gastropoda. Prosobranchia-Neurobranchia (contd.). Indian Museum, Calcutta [=Kolkata], x + 306 pp. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.23978" title="Hand list of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Part II. Gastropoda. Prosobranchia-Neurobranchia (contd.). Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], x + 306 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.23978" year="1885">1885</bibRefCitation>
: 5) was consistent in noting Theobald as the collector of the Pegu specimens, we consider that Theobald was indeed the collector of the holotype and that the label noting Stoliczka as the collector reflects an inadvertent error, perhaps associated with Stoliczka having collected the 
<normalizedToken id="90774A64BDA7653C73054183E8EA5723" originalValue="“Tenasserim”">&quot;Tenasserim&quot;</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="1011CFC8ED33FA4154FB7BDAD640C5AE" originalValue="“Mandalay”">&quot;Mandalay&quot;</normalizedToken>
specimens. 
<bibRefCitation id="E077E5BB2C055FDB25DF9CDBECF861E4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" author="Cowie, RH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B8" refString="Cowie, RH, 2015. The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda. Zootaxa 3940 (1): 1 - 92, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" title="The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" volume="3940" year="2015">Cowie (2015</bibRefCitation>
: 36) treated 
<taxonomicName id="3D7871022253F53919F0F7BECDEBAB0B" authorityName="K.Miller" authorityYear="1879" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria expansa" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis id="61BF645BF39463DE89D3924A5FDBE1C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria expansa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nevill as a synonym of either 
<taxonomicName id="8BA3914FD73021DA213CA7F1C04A8691" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria ampullacea" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ampullacea">
<emphasis id="46CE4B520A02B280C659368741DD8615" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria ampullacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, following 
<bibRefCitation id="3BA8136DCA082B13AE8FF18AD9D67DFA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/oxfordjournals.mollus.a066303" author="Sowerby, GB" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="56 - 64" refId="B29" refString="Sowerby, GB, 1910. Notes on the family Ampullariidae. Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London 9 (1): 56 - 64, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/oxfordjournals.mollus.a066303" title="Notes on the family Ampullariidae." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/oxfordjournals.mollus.a066303" volume="9" year="1910">Sowerby (1910</bibRefCitation>
: 56), or 
<emphasis id="222CFCC23066100D1EAA73CA5F6B1093" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">gracilis</emphasis>
Lea, following 
<bibRefCitation id="497D4C88FEB2DBF1DFDF8747719C7CA5" author="Prashad, B" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" refId="B26" refString="Prashad, B, 1925. Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8(2): 69-89, pls. 13-15. http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" title="Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8 (2): 69 - 89, pls. 13 - 15." url="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" year="1925">Prashad (1925</bibRefCitation>
: 81), but refrained from making a definitive decision, pending further research. The holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="6748DFCDC7992C6A225A0DB055578FC9" authorityName="K.Miller" authorityYear="1879" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria expansa" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis id="ADAC0B6E50BE14B799B5C028B06CDDC5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria expansa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="86256621404D4E390F494964517C682C" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Holotype of Ampullaria conica var. expansa Nevill, 1877; NZSI M. 2426." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.96.47792.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/371731" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4</figureCitation>
) is clearly not 
<taxonomicName id="83144DB666AC8EAFB4D9FCD461DA62FC" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria ampullacea" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ampullacea">
<emphasis id="B0650BC7FB8285BC5CB07B9C707CD8A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria ampullacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on its shell shape. In fact, it seems more likely that 
<taxonomicName id="707925CE88BBF62C2C272B319E23B347" authorityName="K.Miller" authorityYear="1879" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria expansa" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis id="91A27027BFEBC60598ECE220788F7776" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria expansa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of the widespread 
<taxonomicName id="DE28044AF7A2638B02D4FAE13BEA074A" baseAuthorityName="Mousson" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Pila" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pila scutata" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scutata">
<emphasis id="EEBC157F35D8405BC91FEB2247AA3CEA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pila scutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mousson, 1848), which is known from Myanmar (
<bibRefCitation id="6AC5D36E93AF454ADD614D8DB959E065" author="Low, MEY" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="55 - 60" publicationUrl="https://lkcnhm.nus.edu.sg/app/uploads/2017/06/2013nis055-060-5.pdf" refId="B17" refString="Low, MEY, Tan, SK, Ng, TH, 2013. Pila conica (Wood, 1828), or Pila scutata (Mousson, 1848)? The correct name for the native apple snail of Singapore (Gastropoda: Ampullariidae). Nature in Singapore 6: 55 - 60, https://lkcnhm.nus.edu.sg/app/uploads/2017/06/2013nis055-060-5.pdf" title="Pila conica (Wood, 1828), or Pila scutata (Mousson, 1848)? The correct name for the native apple snail of Singapore (Gastropoda: Ampullariidae)." url="https://lkcnhm.nus.edu.sg/app/uploads/2017/06/2013nis055-060-5.pdf" volume="6" year="2013">Low et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
: 56; 
<bibRefCitation id="2D4CC12743E2D150834E78B2D3AD0E66" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" author="Cowie, RH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B8" refString="Cowie, RH, 2015. The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda. Zootaxa 3940 (1): 1 - 92, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" title="The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" volume="3940" year="2015">Cowie 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 47). Nonetheless, we refrain from formally synonymising 
<taxonomicName id="9ACCA310D1EAB56BD82F4B5FE64D1D00" authorityName="K.Miller" authorityYear="1879" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria expansa" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis id="62C7F6D9331BA097FBD84225057806A6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria expansa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nevill with 
<taxonomicName id="0B7E2412F3C1261151B16ACFBCD3AEE2" baseAuthorityName="Mousson" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Pila" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pila scutata" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scutata">
<emphasis id="2B24975994DE145FD97992FF59C5FF0B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pila scutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mousson, pending further, taxonomic research.
</paragraph>
